{# ── DISCLOSURE BANNER · ABOVE THE FOLD (Sheet-7 honest-triage). Canonical .disclosure
     class (03-conversion.css) — the established disclosure-banner treatment reused here.
     The not-the-Tax-Department boundary is also rendered as a checks-list of explicit
     boundaries below, so the disclosure is doubly prominent. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-svc-notice-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure">
      <strong>TechBrot is an independent bookkeeping and Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not the New York State Department of Taxation and Finance, not any government agency, and not a CPA, EA, or tax attorney.</strong> Contacting us does not reach the Tax Department. We do not respond to notices on your behalf, do not represent you before the Department, do not provide tax or legal advice, and do not file returns or protests. We help you understand the notice, reconcile the underlying books, and assemble clean figures your licensed professional uses to respond. This page is educational; it is not legal or tax advice.
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list" id="ny-svc-notice-boundaries">
      <li><strong>What we do:</strong> help you understand what the notice concerns, reconcile the period&rsquo;s books and records, identify discrepancies, and assemble a documented package for your CPA / EA / tax attorney.</li>
      <li><strong>What we do not do:</strong> respond to the notice, file a return or protest, represent you before the Tax Department, or give tax or legal advice &mdash; your licensed professional does all of that.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SHORT VERSION · TL;DR prose. (H2: The short version.) ── #}
